<h2 id="100">7. Editing text elements</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit texts of the plugin in the <strong>CMS » Multilingualism</strong> menu. The texts can be adapted into all available system languages. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adapting language files:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Multilingualism</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On the left side, select the <strong>Source language</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On the right side, select the <strong>Target language</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the sections <strong>messages</strong> and <strong>payment methods</strong> in the <strong>Mollie</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the text for the individual text elements in the area of the target language.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Find more information in how to edit online shop texts on the manual page <a href="/en/online-store/setting-up-ceres#231">Editing online store texts</a>.</p>
</div>
